nodes.bodyText:
A way to save if-clauses might be:
primarySequencer = sequencer; if (!logTails.contains(sequencer)) { break; }
The only difference is that if there is no non-tail servers, your code picks the first sequencer in the loop iteration whereas mine picks the last one. Does this matter?

